00:17:56.710 --> 00:17:59.820
Iran and Iraq to disassemble
bombs out there.

00:17:59.820 --> 00:18:02.250
Just an amazing thing
what they're doing.

00:18:02.250 --> 00:18:06.210
And just a brilliant woman
from MIT, and just really

00:18:06.210 --> 00:18:09.170
changed the way what machines
could think and how they could

00:18:09.170 --> 00:18:10.850
see and they can move.

00:18:10.850 --> 00:18:14.330
And this is just all what she's
thinking about all day.

00:18:14.330 --> 00:18:16.840
"So the neat thing about 3M is
that we have experts in just

00:18:16.840 --> 00:18:18.990
about every field that you
can possibly imagine.

00:18:18.990 --> 00:18:20.840
We've all got these people
who are willing to help.

00:18:20.840 --> 00:18:22.180
But you need to take
advantage. of

00:18:22.180 --> 00:18:23.760
it." Matthew Scholz.

00:18:23.760 --> 00:18:25.560
So he's a researcher at 3M.

00:18:25.560 --> 00:18:28.510
Has anybody ever broken their
arm and had a cast?

